4.71/5  rDev +6.8%look: 5 | smell: 4 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5The beer pours a crystal clear straw golden color with 3 finger white head. Tiny little champagne like bubble continually run up the side of the glass. The nose is an interesting combination of green apple, white grape, and an all encompassing tart funk.
The flavor of this beer is phenomenal. This beer really took on the characteristics of the chardonnay barrel it was aged in. There is tart green apple and white grapes that dominate the flavor. There is a tart lemon mixed in with musty oak and wet leaves. Those flavors may not sound appetizing, but trust me - this beer is fantastic. There is a very dry finish with tons of carbonation.
I was a little apprehensive about this beer, because of all the hype it gets and the cost ($15 for 330ml), but I think it was worth every penny. One of the best American Wild ales I have ever had. I'm going to make it a point to pick up the other three Russian River sours available in the area when I can afford them. 963 charactersjlandis, Oct 25, 2010
