Pours a beautiful deep goldenrod color with two fingers of fluffy white head that lingers in a creamy white layer on top. Leaves a tight, fine lacing on the glass.
Aroma is tart and vinous with just a bit of funkiness in the back if you stick your nose in the glass long enough. This is really intoxicating. I just want to sniff this beer more.
